==Sprite Animation System==

===Hero Animations===

The hero character has 16 different sprites covering:
* 4 directions (up, down, left, right)
* 2 walking frames per direction
* 2 weapon states (armed/unarmed)

Sprite mapping:
{| class="wikitable"
!  Tile ID  !!  Description
|-
|  $00-$03  ||  Hero facing down (unarmed, frames 1-2, armed frames 1-2)
|-
|  $04-$07  ||  Hero facing up (unarmed, frames 1-2, armed frames 1-2)
|-
|  $08-$0B  ||  Hero facing left (unarmed, frames 1-2, armed frames 1-2)
|-
|  $0C-$0F  ||  Hero facing right (unarmed, frames 1-2, armed frames 1-2)
|}

===Monster Animations===

Most monsters use 1-2 tiles:
* Single frame: Slimes, simple creatures
* Two frames: Most humanoid monsters (idle + attack)
* Special: Dragons use multiple frames for breath attacks

===NPC Sprites===

NPCs use shared sprite sets:
* Male villager sprites
* Female villager sprites
* Guard/soldier sprites
* Royal sprites (King, Princess)
* Merchant sprites

