==Graphics Compression==

Dragon Warrior uses minimal graphics compression:
* Sprites are stored as raw 2bpp tile data
* Some background patterns use tile mirroring
* Palette animation used for water/fire effects
* Text uses character-based compression

==Technical Implementation==

===PPU Configuration===
* Background: CHR Bank 1
* Sprites: CHR Bank 0
* Name tables: $2000 (main), $2400 (status)
* Pattern tables: $0000 (sprites), $1000 (background)

===Bank Switching===
MMC1 mapper controls CHR bank selection:
* Fixed mode: Bank 0 for sprites, Bank 1 for background
* CHR banking rarely used in Dragon Warrior

===Color Cycling===
Some tiles use palette animation:
* Water tiles cycle between blue shades
* Torch flames alternate orange/red
* Magic effects use rapid color changes

==Asset Extraction Notes==

When extracting graphics from Dragon Warrior:
* Apply appropriate palette per sprite type
* Monster sprites use Monster Palette (ID 6)
* Hero/NPC sprites use Character Palette (ID 5)
* Items/UI use Menu Palette (ID 4)
* Background tiles use context-specific palettes

